description:

Learn about the city’s history and culture from our knowledgable local guides as you cruise around in our comfy mini coach, hopping out at all the best places to snap photos, including the Space Needle, the Amazon Spheres, The Fremont Troll, the Dragon Gate and more, and of course a vista viewpoint for a shot of the city skyline and Mt. itemListElement.name: Private Nesting Great Blue Herons, Ballard Locks and Gasworks Park Tour!

name: Private Nesting Great Blue Herons, Ballard Locks and Gasworks Park Tour!
description:
Seattle has several colonies of Great Blue Herons across the city, let's go visit the largest one. With 34 nests this year, it's a fantastic opportunity to watch adults and hear the glorious racket of the chicks! Then we'll explore the Hiram Chittenden Locks, a critical component of our maritime industry and history and learn how they transformed Seattle. Then we're off to Gas Works Park for stunning views of the city and unique industrial preservation, before visiting the houseboat communities along Lake Union.

Kids aged 8 and up are welcome, as I do not have car seats for younger ones.

The heron colony disperses after the chicks fledge, so **this tour ends on June 15th**, which is my best guess as to when the nesting season ends.

description: Not long ago a family member would have had a farm you could visit, those days are gone. itemListElement.name: Private Curated Pike Place Market Food Tour

name: Private Curated Pike Place Market Food Tour
description:
Pike Place Market is for everybody, but the pace of Seattle’s historic farmers’ market can be overwhelming for newcomers. Most people simply resort to blogs and restaurant review apps in order to guide them through a new environment, but still you end up spending too much of the day waiting in line and deciding where to go next. 

Think of us as your foodie fast pass to Pike Place Market! You answer a few questions about what types of foods you normally enjoy, and we will curate a special tasting menu based on the preferences of your group. 

We accommodate all dietary considerations, meat-lovers and plant-based alike, picky eaters, sweet tooths and brave explorers. No two tours are the same. 

Our guides have years of experience working in and leading food tours around Pike Place Market. This tour is the ultimate test; a chance for each guide to prove that they have mastered the art of navigating the chaos on cobblestones known locally as “The Market.”

Don’t let us off easy.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Rock and Roll History from Hendrix to Grunge and More

name: Seattle Rock and Roll History from Hendrix to Grunge and More
description:
Relax in a classic Mercedes for a comfy and personal tour guided by me, a Northwest native and former Seattle Times reporter. We'll explore Seattle’s historical Rock & Roll sites ranging from the city’s earliest jazz club, beatnik jazz to Jimi Hendrix growing up poor in Seattle--where a guitar became something of a first and lasting love for him--through our iconoclastically creative (though sometimes tragic) Grunge scene, to great musicians of the present day.

As we go from early Chris Cornell sites, to Kurt Cobain's mansion, to the Jimi Hendrix statue to Layne Staley's penthouse, and a whole lot more, you'll also enjoy an inside tour of Seattle, with great rock stories along the way. 

By the end of the tour, I hope you will have gained a deep appreciation for the art these musicians have created, and a sympathy for the sometimes difficult lives that provided the roots from which their music emerged.

review.name: A unique tour of Seattle
review.reviewBody: A unique tour of Seattle experiencing the sites linked to Jazz, Grunge and More.  Grant was a well-knowledged tour guide on the music details.  We will recommend the trip to friends.

review.name: More than a tour
review.reviewBody:
Our experience went beyond only seeing sights or driving through neighborhoods though we definitely did that. We got a feel for the place through the history and lives of the city's musicians, accompanied by their music playing in the background. Riding in a roomy smooth old Mercedes, Grant wove stories as he wove in and out of traffic. We had conversations about the community and culture.

We stopped at particular places of interest to get out, look more closely, appreciate the cold gray Seattle weather that we decided had to have been a factor in the mood of many songs from the grunge era.  If you are a Jimi Hendrix or Kurt Cobain fan, you have a chance to leave something at their prospective memorials. 

It's a poignant, fun, surprising view of Seattle whether you're a visitor or a resident.

review.name: A Tour of Rock Laughs and “OMG I never knew that” Moments
review.reviewBody: Through history and jokes, Grant showed this 16 year Seattleite a side of this town I never knew.  Grants’s knowledge is unbeatable, with a keen focus on Seattle Grunge scene.  If you really wanna know what inspired SoundGarden’s Chris Cornell to write Black Hole Sun, what connects “We Are the World” to Garfield High School, or if you want to understand the mindset of Kurt Cobain pre and post “Smells like Teen Spirit”—You gotta book now.

review.name: Just wait 20 minutes
review.reviewBody: First, let me thank you Grant for designing such a wonderful and entertaining afternoon! Ever since we got in touch with you, we could see your commitment of making our trip around Seattle back roads as memorable as it could be. It was indeed a smooth ride for us. It felt like you would just wait 20 minutes and the beginning of the next story or song history would unfold. And you were right about stopping by Dick's Drive In near the Golden Oldies Records afterwards!
